  "labScript": "Please fabricate Co-Cr metal framework for maxillary RPD.

Major connector: A-P Strap with 0.5mm beading on the tissue side.

* Exact undercuts to engage are marked in red. *

#2: Mesial proximal plate, Mesial rest, Akers clasp engaging 0.01" DB undercut, Palatal reciprocal clasp.
#4: Distal proximal plate, Distal rest, Akers clasp engaging 0.01" MB undercut, Palatal reciprocal clasp.
#6: Distal proximal plate, Cingulum rest.
#9: Mesial proximal plate, Mesial ball rest.
#11: Mesial proximal plate, Cingulum rest.
#12: Distal proximal plate, Mesial rest, Combination clasp engaging 0.02" MB undercut, Palatal reciprocal plate.

#3: Open lattice.
#5: Open lattice.
#7-8: Open lattice.
#10: Open lattice.
#13-15: Open lattice with distal tissue stop.

Relief: 0.5 mm relief over the incisive papilla and median palatal raphe (mandatory per UIC).
Anterior strap: 6 mm posterior to gingival margins of anterior teeth, 8 mm wide.
Posterior strap: 6 mm anterior to vibrating line, 6-8 mm wide.
Lateral straps: ≥4 mm wide; cross the palate at oblique angle for tongue comfort.
Framework metal thickness: 0.5-1.0 mm Co-Cr at major connector; smooth, polished tongue-facing surface.

Cast clasp arm position: terminal 1/3 in undercut (0.01" engagement); middle 1/3 at survey line; origin 1/3 rigid above survey line. Clasp tip in gingival 1/3 of clinical crown — NOT on gingival margin.

Denture tooth mold (anterior): [Trubyte Classic — TBD at wax-rim try-in based on intercanine distance + high-smile line].
Denture tooth mold (posterior): [Trubyte Classic posterior, e.g. F30 10° — TBD at wax-rim try-in].
Tooth shade: [TBD chairside via Vita shade guide — matched to existing natural teeth].
Acrylic gingival shade: [TBD via UIC gingival shade guide — typically L199-OR or 50% OR + 50% DK mix].

Please return for try-in. Thank you.",
  "majorConnector": {
    "note": "0.5mm beading on tissue side",
    "rationale": "Rigid major connector of choice for Maxillary Kennedy Class I and II (Lecture 6 p. 8). Two transverse straps (8 mm anterior, 6-8 mm posterior) connected laterally provide cross-arch rigidity essential for distal extension support.",
    "tier": "strong",
    "type": "A-P Strap",
    "width": "8mm each strap, 6mm gingival clearance",
  },
  "pdi": {
    "breakdown": {
      "abutmentCondition": {
        "class": "I",
        "rationale": "All bounding abutments have good periodontal prognosis — no preprosthetic therapy required on abutments.",
      },
      "location": {
        "class": "III",
